Two drug gangs who attempted to launch a 'vast' cocaine smuggling operation by targeting a dock worker have been jailed for a total of nearly 150 years.

Ten men - nine gangsters and the worker at Portsmouth Docks, Shaun Wilson - will serve between eight-and-a-half and 20 years each for conspiring to smuggle in millions of pounds of the Class A drug in exotic fruit containers.

Investigators at the National Crime Agency (NCA) said two organised crime groups targeted Wilson, 46, so they could exploit his knowledge of security procedures.

