Others sentenced were Jason Flisher, 43, from Folkestone, Kent (16 years), Richard Edwards, 51, from Barking, east London (20 years) and Eric Ward, 51, from Portsmouth (10 years).

Those involved in the second gang who were sentenced were Errol Heibner, 69, from Bow, East London and Norman Burton, 57, from Catford, south London, who were both jailed for 14 years.

Donald Chambers, from Charlton, was jailed for 13 years.

The total of all the men's sentences was 149-and-a-half years.

A further two men were convicted of money laundering offences after being arrested at the Channel Tunnel as part of the wider operation. They were handed suspended sentences.  

